2012-12-01 15:03  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Index.pm: Index.pm: failsafe "die" for bad cache
	  initialisation

	  Added "die" statements in case symbol cache not properly
	  initialized in setdymdeclaration and setsymreference. Should
	  never fire since the symbols are supposed to have already been
	  seen. This is only for debugging. Lines could be withdrawn once
	  it is proven caching code is always correct.

