	  Apache:: which is deprecated in mod_perl version 2)

2012-11-02 18:22  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Files.pm: Files.pm: add "dot" dirs discarding to
	  _ignoredirs()

2012-11-02 09:11  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Files.pm, Files/CVS.pm, Files/GIT.pm, Files/Plain.pm,
	  Files/Subversion.pm: Files.pm, Files/*.pm (except BK.pm): common
	  factor filter for ignored directories

	  Create common method _ignoredirs in the super class so that
	  ignored dirs are handled in a single location for easier
	  maintenability. Also all file backends will exhibit same
	  behaviour. However, BK is not updated since current maintainer
	  has no means to test changes.

2012-11-02 09:00  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Files/GIT.pm: GIT.pm: files beginning wit dot or ending
	  with tilde not filtered out (bug #3580435)

	  Bad copy-and-paste when creating package: reference to wrong
	  variable $node instead of $entryname

2012-10-31 18:28  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang.pm: Lang.pm: tab hint from filrtype.conf not
	  effective (bug #3581966)

	  Caused by wrong attempt to capture last value of iteration
	  variable in foreach block. Fixzd by transfer of value into
	  another local variable.

2012-10-31 18:14  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Config.pm: Config.pm: fix for bug 3581487

	  When LXR is the root site (as http://host/source), 'virtroot'
	  ends up as an empty string which cannot match a script patch
	  equal to /. Fix: both script path and 'virtroot' are given a
	  canonical form with an initial / (thus any empty string is
	  transformed into /)

2012-09-30 16:43  tag release-1-0-0

2012-09-30 16:43  ajlittoz

	* genxref: genxref: fix a small typo

2012-09-30 10:33  ajlittoz

	* templates/html/: config-head-btn-smaller.html,
	  html-head-btn-smaller.html, html-head-btn.html,
	  html-head-smaller.html, html-head.html, html-tail.html:
	  templates/html-head-*, /html-tail.html: turn references to
	  LXRimages HTML-relative

	  HTML-absolute references are not reliable when LXR is not rooted
	  at DocumentRoot. This does not mean HTML-relative references are
	  valid in any server-configuration, but they cover the most
	  frequent cases.

