2012-09-22 07:49  ajlittoz

	* scripts/Tagger.pm: Tagger.pm: moved and optimized

	  Moved to scripts/directory since it is used only by genxref Add
	  symbol cache management to improve indexing speed.

2012-09-21 17:17  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Files.pm, Files/Subversion.pm: Files.pm,
	  Files/Subversion.pm: add Subversion support

2012-09-21 17:14  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Files/GIT.pm: GIT.pm: cosmetic change in syntax and
	  comments

2012-09-21 17:11  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Files/: CVS.pm, GIT.pm, Plain.pm: Files/CVS.pm, /GIT.pm,
	  /Plain.pm: fix syntax for 'ignoredirs' access

2012-09-21 17:07  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang/Generic.pm: Generic.pm: remove method
	  processreserved()

	  There is no region named 'reserved'; this method appears to be a
	  remnant of an ancient design. Reserved words are now processed by
	  function isreserved() called from processxxx() methods. The
	  function has also followed generic.conf evolutions.

2012-09-21 16:48  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang/Generic.pm: Generic.pm: case-insensitive language

	  Conversion to upper-case missing for "relation" (aka. member of)
	  symbol

2012-09-21 08:18  ajlittoz

	* showconfig, lib/LXR/Config.pm, lib/LXR/Template.pm,
	  templates/html/html-config.html: showconfig, Config.pm,
	  Templates.pm, templates/html/html-config.html: fix for bug
	  3570203 (incorrect tree links in showconfig)

	  Create a new method $config->treeurl from code already present in
	  Template.pm for tree "speed switch" buttons. This sets up a
	  correct URL, ready to display the correct tree after a mode
	  button click.  Simultaneously, fix enumeration and highlighting
	  of configuration parameters with "force all" option.

2012-09-17 16:11  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang/: Cobol.pm, Generic.pm: Generic.pm, Cobol.pm:
	  preliminary implementation of case-insensitive languages

	  Symbols are entered upper-case in the DB and request is against
	  upper-case version of symbol. OK for source.	ident not modified,
	  consequently identifier search is bound to fail (will not match
	  upper-case version of identifier or, if identifier upper-cased,
	  will not match symbols with differing cases).

2012-09-17 13:26  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Template.pm: Template.pm: propagate identifier name

	  Propagate _i=identifier_name in ident's button links to avoid
	  retyping identifier after a change in variables state.

2012-09-17 13:17  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang/Python.pm: Lang.pm, Lang/*: restructure classes and
	  comment them Markup.pm: recover language name from description

	  Better isolate each language parsing from the others; allow to
	  requeue a fragment tail for new processing if needed (this avoids
	  recursive processing); use consistently 'identdef' for identifier
	  parsing; add Python parser and improve the others

2012-09-17 12:15  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Lang.pm, Markup.pm, Lang/Generic.pm, Lang/Perl.pm,
	  Lang/Ruby.pm: Lang.pm, Lang/*: restructure classes and comment
	  them Markup.pm: recover language name from description

	  Better isolate each language parsing from the others; allow to
	  requeue a fragment tail for new processing if needed (this avoids
	  recursive processing); use consistently 'identdef' for identifier
	  parsing; add Python parser and improve the others

2012-09-17 12:01  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Common.pm: Common.pm: failsafe fixes

	  Guarantee 'path_info' is never empty: remplace "no paths" by '/'
	  for root directory. Thus, test for a trailing slash is a correct
	  way to test for directory when Index.pm not yet initialised
	  (can't then use isfile() or isdirectory()) Add a call to
	  $index->final_cleanup() to disconnect gracefully from database.

2012-09-17 11:56  ajlittoz

	* lib/Local.pm: Local.pm: use getfilehandle

	  Make use of file handle to the target file instead of repeatedly
	  passing its name and directory; results in a better performance
	  (though marginal)

2012-09-17 11:51  ajlittoz

	* source: source: prepare for Subversion

	  Subversion getfiletime() will return a formatted string instead
	  of a number of seconds since epoch. Sub modtime() must be adapted
	  to handle both formats.

2012-09-17 11:48  ajlittoz

	* source: source: prepare for Subversion

	  Subversion always needs to known the selected version for a file.
	  Consequently, add $releaseid argument to getauthor(), renaming
	  this former argument $rev[ision] which better describes its
	  content.

2012-09-17 11:46  ajlittoz

	* ident: ident, search: cosmetic

	  Cleanup syntax

2012-09-17 11:44  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Files.pm, Files/BK.pm, Files/CVS.pm, Files/GIT.pm:
	  Files.pm, BK.pm, CVS.pm, GIT.pm: prepare for Subversion

	  Subversion always needs to known the selected version for a file.
	  Consequently, add $releaseid argument to getauthor(), renaming
	  this former argument $rev[ision] which better describes its
	  content.

2012-09-17 11:32  ajlittoz

	* ident, search: ident, search: cosmetic

	  Cleanup syntax

2012-09-17 11:16  ajlittoz

	* diff: diff: uneeded extra parameter on call for markupfile

	  Remove spurious third parameter to markupfile (remnant of old
	  implementation?)

2012-09-10 17:36  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Template.pm: Template.pm: Keep variable value not listed
	  in 'range'

	  In CVS, directories are not associated with a version. To avoid
	  restoring 'version' selection, the value any variable has on
	  entry is kept, even if not in 'range'. Thus sequence display
	  file-then directory-then file stays in the same version instead
	  of reverting to 'head'.  Also cosmetic changes to file.

2012-09-10 17:22  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Index.pm, Index/Mysql.pm, Index/Oracle.pm,
	  Index/Postgres.pm, Index/SQLite.pm: Index.pm, Index/*.pm: Move
	  common methods to Index.pm; add methods for incremental indexing

	  Common factor all DB-engine independent queries, keeping in the
	  specific DB-backends only the idiosyncratic queries, notably
	  those related with auto-increment since the syntax is specific to
	  an engine.  Add methods to correctly erase definitions and usages
	  in selected files of a single revision (to be used by genxref for
	  incremental indexing).

2012-09-08 08:52  ajlittoz

	* source, lib/LXR/Common.pm: source, Common.pm: do not lose
	  selected version under CVS when displaying directories

	  If a version is selected before displaying a directory, keep it
	  into variable 'v' though CVS does not manage directory version,
	  so that a file is listed with this preselected version. Version
	  check is deferred until a file is displayed.

	  Also, change for shorter syntax in hash reference

2012-08-27 08:59  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXRversion.pm, lib/LXR/Common.pm, lib/LXR/Template.pm,
	  scripts/set-lxr-version.sh: Set LXR version through scripting

	  LXR version set directly into Template.pm with script
	  set-lxr-version.sh (which can revert file to template state).
	  LXRversion.pm no longer needed.

2012-08-18 15:47  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/SimpleParse.pm: SimpleParse.pm - Mark more explicitly the
	  5.10-feature blocks

2012-08-18 15:44  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Config.pm: Config.pm - Incorrect URL scanning

	  Since scheme (http[s]:) is optional in URL, make its presence
	  scanning also optional.

2012-08-05 11:45  ajlittoz

	* scripts/initial-config.sh: scripts/initial-config.sh - Wrong
	  'usage' text

	  Change for correct usage of script

2012-08-04 14:26  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/SimpleParse.pm: SimpleParse.pm: allow more complex
	  rexexps in language specification

	  WARNING: possible only by using Perl 5.10 feature which causes
	  incompatibility for people still using Perl 5.8. Without this
	  feature, it is impossible to cope with Ruby %()-string lexical
	  form.

	  Workaround if Ruby (or any other language dependent on the
	  feature) is not needed: use previous version of SimpleParse.pm
	  and remove Ruby (or other dependent language) description from
	  generic.conf AND filetype.conf. You can be smarter in removing
	  only the offending descriptions from the language 'spec' in
	  generic.conf to keep a partial parsing.

2012-08-03 17:25  ajlittoz

	* search: Search: unable to search for a string containing space

	  Bug 3551992: after <FORM> submission, the search string is
	  encoded as per HTML protocol (spaces changed to + signs). The
	  search string encoding must be reversed before using it.

2012-08-03 16:33  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Common.pm, Config.pm, Markup.pm, SimpleParse.pm:
	  Common.pm, Config.pm, Markup.pm, SimpleParse.pm

	  Document and clean-up source code SimpleParse.pm, in sub
	  nextfrag, ensure safe transition at end of "code" fragment in all
	  circumstances.

