	  to ! since $ causes malfunction on some OSes (creates a
	  void-named variable whose value is garbage when sent back as LXR
	  state)

2012-02-23 07:49  ajlittoz

	* genxref: genxref: incorrect test on ctags version If Exuberant
	  ctags is not installed (but plain ctags is), check fails on title
	  line of ctags, leaving $1 undefined which prints an empty
	  version. Then version extraction is done from the title line,
	  which defines $1. Test for version succeeds unhappily on
	  erroneous data.  Corrected as: transfer version information from
	  the result of title line chach; add a !defined() test.

2012-02-11 08:59  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang.pm: Lang.pm: common factor <span> tagging for
	  elements spanning several lines

2012-02-11 08:12  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang/generic.conf: generic.conf: Perl parsing, needs to
	  handle escaped characters in regexp operators (aka. m// or s///)
	  at least for LXR itself

2012-02-10 20:59  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/Lang/generic.conf: generic.conf: Perl parsing, add 'atom'
	  production to swallow quote and regexp operators.  NOTE: this fix
	  can't handled all cases (notably properly nested braces when
	  delimiters are also braces). No attempt has been made to skip
	  escaped characters for performance of the regexp; that means we
	  can get early termination if escaped character is the delimiter.

2012-02-10 20:54  ajlittoz

	* lib/LXR/: Lang.pm, Markup.pm: Lang.pm, Markup.pm: create a
	  processstring sub analogous to processcomment to avoid marking
	  line number when string spans several line (add a </span> before
	  \n and reopen with <span class='string'> immediately after.

